Cherry Sorbet

4 c cherries, pitted and halved
1/2 c sugar
1 tbsp lemon juic
1 c club soda

Puree cherries, sugar and lemon juice in food processor or blender.  Pour into 2-quart saucepan; bring to a boil and cook 3 min. Cool thoroughly.  Stir in club soda.  Pour into shallow 8" baking pan; freeze 1 1/2 hrs or until edges are solid but center is slushy.  Spoon frozen mixture into food processor or blender; process to a coarse texture.  Freeze 1 1/2 hrs or until edges are solid but center is slushy.  Repeat processing step.  Freeze 6 hrs or longer.

Notes: Recipe easily doubled. Can split mixture into 2 pans to freeze faster.

Nutrition
Calories: 204
Protein: 2g
Fat: 13g
Carbohydrates: 50g
Fiber: 2g
Cholesterol: 0mg
Sodium: 12mg
